,Not Recommended,214250,26594248,"Posted: 13 November, 2016",all,D3nni,"About The GameHere's 5 hours of my life that I'll never get back. I managed to put off buying this game and avoiding all spoilers for about 4 years now. After finishing the game, I kinda wish I had saved my $3.75 and watched a playthrough instead.When it comes Ubisoft games, it's either a hit and miss for me. I Am Alive, unfortunately, falls under the ""miss"" category. For a game that brings such an interesting atmosphere and mechanics to the table, if fails to execute on them.The PC port is also horrendous. Good luck having a smooth playthrough playing an any OS that's beyond Windows 7. Playing on Windows 10, I encountered several crashes upon reaching a checkpoint, some of which, caused me to start the entire level over.Story SpoilersThe story does not quite make any sense to me. The main character is somewhere on the east coast to begin the game. After some sort of apocalypse, where humanity is nearly brought to the brink of extinction; think The Walking Dead, but instead of zombies, it's dust, earthquakes, and famine; he spends the better part of a year walking across the US to find his wife and daughter back at home on the west coast. The entire time, he has a camcorder that he uses to document his adventure. During several cutscenes, you can see someone watching the videos in what appears to be current time, so all of this takes place in the past. Upon arriving back in his hometown of Haventon, he finds the city in ruin, yet he still expects his family to be sitting at home waiting for him. After surprisingly finding that they're not there, he comes across a lost girl roaming the streets. Among all the thugs roaming the streets that will shoot you on sight, he takes it upon himself to help the little girl out. Long story short, the little girl has lost her mother, whom you have to rescue, from what I take is a newly established apocalypse brothel. So while you're busy doing fetch quests for other people, you seem to have forgotten about your mission of finding your own family. After about 4-5 hours, the game kinda ends anticlimactically. You get the girl and her mother to safety. It cuts back to the camcorder again and finally zooms out, where what seems to be your wife(?) is watching it while crying, all the while all your gear and whatnot is on a table behind her, which brings me to the assumption that the main character is dead. There is no secret/alternate ending that can be unlocked, as far as I know. Lost had a better ending that this.VerdictI Am Alive was suppose to be a franchise that would stand alongside Far Cry and Assassin's Creed. But after it horrendoues development cycle of delays and being scrapped, we're left with this. Ubisoft managed to scrap the entire full retail version, but later decided to bring it back as what is basically an XBL Arcade game. After it's all said and done, I'd recommend saving your money by not purchasing this game. If you're still truly interested in it, then watch a playthrough on YouTube.4/10"
,Not Recommended,214250,360973,"Posted: 4 January, 2013",all,LIKEUCARE,"I Am Alive... or Am I Dead?Ok, game that was in development for a really long time. Heck it was announced at E3 2008 and the game had been shadowing the gaming industry for a long while; even having rumors of cancellation. Alas, it finally got out on consoles at first, then on PC in September 2012.So what is this game? You play as some dude, returning to Havington, a year later after some ""EVENT"" occured. No info about what the event is... So you head to that city to find your lost wife and daughter only to stumble upon an asian kid and her mother. Then you go around and try to keep them safe while fighting some other survivors that made gangs.PROS:-The setting is nice, dust everywhere so the cataclismic feel is there.-Ambiance, sounds, voice acting and even the graphics are decent.-Inventory management-Decent action and can threat enemies with empty gunCONS:-Poor checkpoint system-Poor ""retry mode"" system that if you die and out of ""retries"", you restart till last checkpoint.-Mouse look in this game is atrocious and even freeze often-Exploration is pointless as you need to go into toxic street levels that drains your stamina, only to find soda cans that replenish stamina.-Very linear.-Gangs only agressive vs you and not other gangs.-Crap ending.Worth buying?ONLY at discount! I Am Alive can provide you a good 5-7 hours of playtime... more if you seek to help every refugees.RATING: 5 / 10===SPOILER ALERT===The final cinematic of the game ends with a character crying. There is a good reason for that – I Am Alive is such a waste of a great concept."
