,Recommended,214250,11424723,"Posted: 26 July, 2014",all,routeshell,"I was really impressed by this game. It's immense atomsphere of post-apocalyptic city with no usual zombies aboard just made me forget about all the weak spots (and there are lots of them). Really deep immersion into the setting. You feel alone, scared and depressed all the time. As I already mentioned there are no zombies or aliens or any other fictional stuff. It is a sad grey quest through desolated concrete jungle filled with murderers, rapists and few normal people who are mostly busy with... well, dying. Some gameplay mechanics (such as stamina loss when climbing or suffocating on the bottom levels covered with dust) came out to be very good ideas for making the game closer to real life. Lack of supplies makes it more challenging - you won't be running around with pockets full of different types of ammo and various goods.However, if we speak about the tech part, I Am Alive is far from perfect. I would say that the graphics are very avearge for a product of 2012. It feels more like a game of 2008. The makers did pretty bad job for a product that has been in development for like 5 or 6 years. Sometimes it felt like the they didn't put much effort in this title (especially when everyone were waiting for The Last of Us which came out a year later).Anyway, I do recommend this game for anyone who likes post-apocalyptic settings. It has a unique atmosphere and is definitely worth trying."
,Not Recommended,214250,31008461,Posted: 7 April,all,Danger Dave,"I Am Alive starts off well but slowly goes down hill.It's a mixed bag with a lot to like but also a lot to dislike, the game is short and lacks replayability.It gives the illusion of being an Open World but is completely linear, never really fully exploiting its setting.NPCs are a bit meh, you're forced to basically kill most people that you meet, nothing you do really matters, and the story ends abruptly on a cliffhanger.Its not an awful game but it is awful that it seems so close to being a good game if it had a bit more direction given to it during development.I would recommend either getting Deadlight instead or buying this game when its heavily discounted."
,Recommended,214250,29136778,Posted: 9 January,all,Rocketpants,"This game is really good, one of a handful of games I've ever played that really surprised me. You can read more in-depth reviews by others, I'll just say that I Am Alive is not really like anything else you've ever played before.It has two gameplay elements that really got me hooked - one is the climbing, which is not anything like Tomb Raider or Uncharted. It is puzzle solving and stamina management and sometimes incredibly tense. The other thing I loved is the rarity of bullets - you get maybe a handful throughout the entire game and so you are forced into situations where you might use your single bullet to kill one enemy in the hopes it scares the hell out of the other two that were with him. It might work or it might not. You never get into firefights, you get into very intense standoffs and any hesitation on your part will get you killed.Cons? The game looks like trash, ends very suddenly and is quite liniar. It's not Fallout. But I was very impressed by the gameplay ideas the devs of I Am Alive had and it's too bad the game didn't get more critical success. I would have loved to see a sequel with a better budget."
