76561198009430218,Not Recommended,214250,9900465,"Posted: 22 April, 2014",all,JacoRay,"Before reading my review, first thing you need to do is watch the E3 trailer from 2008.http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HZ6Aely9YrQDid you watch it? Looks great right? I remember E3 2008 and said to myself, ""This game looks great!"", although I knew it was a cinematic trailer, it was the initial concept of survival and escape from hordes of other humans that were possibly your friends prior to ""The Event"", as it's called in the published version of the game, that stood out to me.The game we got? Well, it went through a lot of changes as it was already in development for like, five years prior to E3 2008, and then released in 2012, went through even more changes. The biggest change is that you don't experience ""The Event"", okay, it's a big f*cking earthquake. But how awesome would it have been to experience that as part of the game?Instead, I Am Alive takes place a year later as your character returns to the city of Haventon to find his wife and daughter, how original. Instead, you find some girl named Mei who's just crying in the playground by your house, so you help her find her mother instead, as well as some bloke in a wheelchair.During the game, you can help strangers that actually need it, or kill people that are hostile. It's a very black and white game, literally too. Instead of the nice, yet muddy, colors of the initial trailer, Ubisoft Shanghai rapes your eyes with an over abundance of black and white, mostly white, film grain. The dust is thick, foggy thick.Let me remind you that this game came out in 2012. The textures and models from Super Mario Sunshine are better, and that was 2002. The gameplay tries to emulate the Assassin's Creed climbing, but somehow messes that up. And the shooting mechanic switches you from 3rd person survival game, to 1st person shooter.This game's just doesn't really do anything right, except for the limited ammo which would make sense considering the stuff doesn't just appear out of nowhere.It's mediocre.5/10"
