,Not Recommended,214250,11346924,"Posted: 21 July, 2014",all,Les Grossman,"Lets start with the good things as there are few.1. The levels itself - are in itself atmospheric, it really gives you the impression how a town could look like after a series of earthquakes.2. The climbing mechanic - that you loose endurance/stamina if you climb is a nice change.3. Overall interesting take on survival in a town after a global catastrophic event - without the obligatory zombies.Yeah...that's it.Now to go on with the bad things where do I start:The graphics are washed up and even if you use the highest settings you can't change the fact that this piece of crap was meant to be played on an XBOX or PS2. Yes I know - it is developed for the XBOX 360 and PS3 but I can't drop the feeling that I have seen better graphics in part on a XBOX or PS2.The music at the beginning is good and adds to the little bit of atmosphere there is at all - but it gets so repetitive after a time (especially as you loose stamina constantly and with you loosing stamina the music builds up and always the same tune) that you sometimes just want to mute the whole game.So now we know that the game itself is just a common stone between pearls and diamonds in terms of audio and graphics, but there are these rare jewels that suck at this too but still have great gameplay and story.This game is absolutely NOT one of them.The gameplay is overall horrific with the exception of the climbing mechanic.Combat or stealth - it gives you no choice - you have to fight.There is no sneaking (although they implemeted the sneak button how cool is that) at all, the moment you pass a certain point the game spawns enemies and you can not get around them either because they detect you on the spot or you desperately try to get by the ones that are already somewhere in the level - and the level is created so that you have to get through them.This is no ""THIEF"" at all.So lets ""fight"" which comes down to coerce the AI in getting stuck or other ""special"" movements.Why?Because you either have guns - for which you practically never have any ammunition or you can use your mighty machete.Nonono, not hacking and slashing, you have to wait until your enemies have reached you and then you can draw your machete for one hit.If it is someone with a machete he will block it and you have to go through button smashing, it is easier if the enemy has a gun, then no button smashing.The only problem is that these guys come in packs.So the moment you have to buttonsmash and are locked in the scripted killscene, our enemies friends are hacking you to pieces OR his gun equipped buddies just kill you with one shot (ok,ok @ higher difficulty)The AI can shoot at you forever but if you loot them they magically have emptied everything they had after 1001 shots (one of the many bugs in this game shows you that fact when you get stuck somewhere in a wall and they use you as invincible target practice or you just run around eating up your health items just to see how often they can fire) if you are lucky there is one bullet left after you killed them, about 50% of the time the gun is empty although the owner of it WILL kill you with it if you believe that you could reload the level and just walk past by him.Yes I have the feeling that the people working at this game desperately wanted to shoot themeselves after they saw what they had created and implemented this thoughtful underlying message of the last bullet.You can get a shotgun in the game but first you really have to do some climbing and exploring and the few shots you have are the only ones in the whole game.After around 75% of the game you get a bow with one arrow - oh and you won't believe it - YES!! you can reuse that arrow.The story is pretty mediocre, you should have encountered it somewhere else already and probably better told but worst of all it is pretty shortlived (around 8 hours and I took my sweet time) and cut at the end.The ending is one bad joke.I couldn't help but think that at some point of production they really believed they had born a new superloved AAA title hence the dream of producing dlcs and a second game.But when at the end they realized what a boring abomination they helped to bring into this gamingworld they just hurried up and forced some kind of ending in and a really bad one too.The bottom line is that if you really want to try out this game buy it in a Steam Sale...for up to 3 $/€.Anything more will make you wish you had tossed that money in a blender and watched it blend - more entertainment for the buck."
,Recommended,214250,9267450,"Posted: 26 February, 2014",all,Rupti,"This game has a lot of flaws, but it still manages to create a unique experience unlike anything you've ever played.Unlike most post-apocalyptic games, you don't have any zombies or monsters to fight. Your biggest enemies are the environment, the lack of resources and the other survivors.Getting places is hard. Roads are blocked and bridges are broken, and your climbing skills are the only thing keeping you alive. Problem is, you have a very limited amount of stamina that drains every time you climb or run, and when it's drained fully - you fall. As if that's not enough, dust storms make the air outside unbreathable, and when inside the fog your stamina will constantly drain until you die, or reach high ground.Resources are very limited, and you will rarely have more than 2-3 bullets in your gun. You will often have none. Combat is not based on who shoots faster, but on psychology and bluffing. Raise your hands to let the enemy come near enough for a surprise attack, or aim your empty pistol at him and tell him to back off up to a cliff, then push him over.This combat system makes you get very creative when fighting 5-6 enemies, since you probably wont have enough bullets to kill them all.Some survivors will only fight you if you get too close, and backing off will prevent a fight. Others will ask for your help, and you will have to choose wether or not to spare your very limited supplies.With this combat system and the constant pressure of the draining stamina, this game keeps you stressed throughout it all. And as if that's not enough - you have a limited number of retries before having to restart from the beginning of the chapter!The game is flawed, though:Controls can be a bit clunky while climbing, sometimes resulting in a pointless death and waste of retry.It's not always clear where to go, especially in heavy dust where you can't see♥♥♥♥♥♥ and you might end up walking in circles trying to find the entrance to a building, and it can get quite frustrating.The story is very lacking. You learn pracitcally nothing about what actually happened and the story just seems to stop rather than end when you finish the game.While the game is semi-openworld, you have little to no motivation to explore. Yeah, you might find other survivors or some food and water, but is it really worth running around in a dust storm for?Overall, this game is a solid 8/10 and I highly recommend playing it."
