,Not Recommended,214250,29126608,Posted: 8 January,all,🍎,"This is a great game with a great idea behind it. However, its main downfall is its incompatibility issues with the modern operating systems to date. I've had it crash on me multiple times and luckily, I was on a checkpoint that was fairly close to where I originally was prior to the crash. However, the latest crash had me set back so far. This game has so much potential for those who can actually play it without any probability of a crash. Any way, aside from me bashing on this game's compatibility issues, it is a great game. It requires you to make use of your resources and to not make haste when faced with a potentially deadly situation. Ammunition is extremely hard to come by and killing someone with a machete isn't so easy. I enjoy that sense of tediousness to figure out which opponent actually deserves a bullet and thereafter, eliminate the other opposing threats. The concept of oxygen preservation seems extremely accurate and realistic in areas that contain a thicker volumity to its atmosphere. All in all -- great story, fair graphics, fair game. Just be advised that crashes will exist if you're on a more modern operating system."
