,Recommended,214250,811544,"Posted: 18 September, 2012",all,mark | dj.,"Despite reading mixed reviews of this game I was surprised it was actually this good. The world has been struck by earthquakes and it's up to you, a survivor, to try and find your family.The graphics are dark and moody; you can only see a few metres ahead which makes it difficult to differentiate friend from foe. It really adds to the tension. That, and the lack of bullets. You have to pick targets carefully, and even decide if you want to kill them. It's not always needed, you see, and you really need to preserve your ammo.There are also other survivors to be found and they might need your help. It's up to you. Helping them will grant you a retry. So in the event that you are killed you'll be able to try it again.Besides killing and helping people you'll be climbing around like the PoP and AC games, which feels natural by now, and is cool.Too bad the game is a bit short; it will take most people around 4-6 hours to complete.Yet another game that has to be experienced, people.[Rating: 81/100]"
