,Not Recommended,214250,9192974,"Posted: 20 February, 2014",all,ThWiplash,"Let's just start of by saying that I Am Alive is basically TLoU Lite (even though it came out much earlier). You're in a crapsack world, almost everyone is out to kill you, you take care of a little girl, go on platforming/climbing jaunts, and have a painfully limited supply of ammunition.Where I Am Alive falls apart is the story. The skeleton of something that could be really good is in here, somewhere, and you catch glimpses of it during your (short) stay in Haventon. Unfortunately, the story is never quite brought to fruition. Protracted delays in development, budget cuts, and a final rushed release (as an XBLA release instead of a full retail) all likely contributed to what is IMO an unfinished game.The game isn'tbadper se, it just doesn't do anything particularly well. The platforming could definitely have been done better; the stamina system is interesting, but I found far too many regen items and pitons (which you can use to rest while climbing to regain stamina) to make it really worthwhile. In the end, the whole system seems like a hindrance to my enjoyment of the game, rather than a useful mechanic. Combat is fairly basic, and usually boils down to picking off the people with firearms first, and then pushing the others off of cliffs or stabbing them. The rush you get from your first few hold-ups fades pretty quickly when you realize that EVERY encounter is the same.I would (possibly) have excused all of this had the story been more fleshed out. The ending seems absolutely shoe-horned in after the team ran out of funding.I find it hard to recommend this game to anyone, given how poorly it ends."
76561197966105913,Not Recommended,214250,17786662,"Posted: 29 August, 2015",all,Revixy,The design decisions in this title crippled the games otherwise interesting plot.I'd spend my money on something else. If I were you.
76561198068431321,Not Recommended,214250,31566307,Posted: 5 May,all,mijxero,"I know its apocolyptic, but everything hurts my eyes.  It has an impressive level of screen tearing I've never seen before.  Its clunky and it loves to crash."
,Recommended,214250,2398585,"Posted: 10 January, 2013",all,Cade,"I Am Alive? More like I Am Alpha!Because it's a clearly rushed product that's not very well optimized, is ugly, is short as hell and ends strangely and abruptly.It's also one of the best B-games I've ever played.I Am Alive drops you into a world torn asunder by a cataclysmic event. You're just a guy looking for people from his past, trying to help those in need, and trying to survive in a harsh reality where everything's out to get you. Your main ability is climbing, and the climbing system of IAA is really well-done: it controls a lot like Uncharted or Tomb Raider, but with the addition of a Stamina system: the longer you climb, the more your bar depletes. If it gets to the end, you'll still be able to climb, but your maximum stamina capacity will slowly dwindle until you get to a resting spot. You can restore your max stamina with items, but it's a neat take on providing urgency to a system that's been used before.The combat is the second tier of the game, and it's also exceptionally well-done: the game utilizes an Intimidation system, which allows you to bluff your opponents using an empty gun while you try to control fights to your favor. Sometimes they'll call your bluff, and you'll have to either shoot them or go for a machete kill; other times, you might want to approach hostiles unarmed, wait for one to get close, and then attack with your machete, surprising everyone and giving you the upper hand. Ammo is scarce, and you don't want to waste a bullet: chances are if you miss a shot, you're about to die. The guns feel good, and the fact that unarmored foes die in one hit is an absolutely incredible way of finally adding realistic gunplay, which makes every encounter memorable. If you come across guys with guns, you either need to be unarmed and hope they come to search you or shoot them first. You will probably die a few times before you get the hang of things, and enemies flanking you might surprise you.You later get a bow, which leads to interesting combat encounters since arrows are recoverable and the bow is silent.The story, largely, is told by victims you save and the few friendly people you encounter on your journey and is well-written. The dynamic you have with the first friendly character you meet is the best, leading you to develop an emotional attachment to them. It's not going to win any awards, but it certainly helps to keep you motivated.The game's not without its flaws, however; the ending is rushed, unsatisfying, and leaves you with a lot of questions, and there are times when the checkpoint system can get very annoying. I played the game on Normal and it was pretty tough, but I never had to restart a chapter. There are segments where you wander aimlessly through the streets, hoping to find something climbable to either save you from the dust storms or lead you to the next destination. The game is also (not, in my eyes, a negative) very short (I clocked in at 4h059s) which could leave some people thinking they overpaid.I really liked my time within I Am Alive's world, and a fully-developed sequel or spin-off in the same world would be more than welcome.8/10 Bows and Bullets"
76561198027692026,Recommended,214250,17966051,"Posted: 10 September, 2015",all,Jamez,"Pros:+ Atmosphere of abandonment, decline and hopelessness. Felt like LIMBO at times.+ The character feels like a veteran post apocalyptic survivor.+ Story is simple but believable.+ Well built environment. The urban setting looks like it's gone through hell.+ Loved the climbing which was one of the best features of the game.+ Enemy encounters feel very realistic. You barely make it out alive.Cons:- There were problems with the climbing mechanics. I wish it would have felt smoother and not so rigid. Also keys would not register at times.- Didn't really like the saving system, I would have enjoyed more control there.Verdict:It's a highly tactical post-apocalyptic survival game with a wonderful atmosphere. It's got a wonderful setting and some quite original features."
