76561197991921123,Recommended,214250,13291278,"Posted: 8 December, 2014",all,meshuggah12345,"I Am Alive is easily one of my favorite games, it has a decent plot and fairly well acted voice-overs. The gameplay is a mix of Resident Evil style scavenging and Prince of Persia-esque climbing sections.Your characters stamina bar plays a huge part in how you play this game. Most every action causes it to drain. Running, climbing, and struggling to break locks. When you enter the areas the NPC's refer to as ""the fog"", which is dust and ash in the air caused by storms your stamina constantly drains. Do you risk a few more moments searching dusty streets for vital resources, or climb back up to saftey and let it recharge? You will find yourself constantly watching it well into the later ares of this game.You will come across other survivors and you must decide what to do. Some may be hostlie, some may need help, the intimatation combat is very well done in this game. You are actually able to hold hostiles at gunpoint even when you may not have any ammo. Don't wait too long to act or they may realize your gun is empty and attack.I am currently on my second playthrough of this one and still get the feelings I got when playing it the first time.  Fear, panic, sadness... all are present here throughout the entire game. You never feel overly powerful even after getting some of the better gadgets and weapons. The downside to this game is the rather low resolution textures. However seeing that this is and always has been a $15 dollar title, It can be forgiven as the game is thouroughly entertaining."
