76561198049838287,Not Recommended,214250,28261551,"Posted: 8 December, 2016",all,dajayosan,"Doggone this game pisses me off, primarily because the save system is so erratic and unpredictable.  I ended up doing the same things over and over again, simply because I don't have countless hours to wander around until I can finallly find a save point.  Even then a found save point is no guarantee that, if you log off entirely, that it won't throw you back to some vague save point from the past.  Very very frustrating with no sense whatsoever.  That coupled with the mouse usage in a fight or when lifting a door - you have to tap the LMB furiously to accomplish your task and believe me you can't do it with just your index finger resting on the LMB.  NOOOOO!!!  I have to hit ""E"", grab the mouse with my Left hand, then using my Right index finger, pound the LMB into submission.  And half the time that doesn't work either.  Games should be FUN, not endless repetitive work, so I'm giving this game a resounding thumbs down.  It's not a pretty game, the graphics and landscape interaction are minimal, and most of the time everything is shrowded in fog.  Pointless, simply pointless.If you insist on playing this game here's a suggestion.  Play it on EASY.  The reason to do so is simple.  On any other level the only way you get to continue after you die, and you WILL die many many times, is if you accumulate ""Replays"" by saving somebody.  This is the ONLY benefit of saving somebody!  On EASY you get INFINITE REPLAYS.  That is the ONLY change in the game, so why not?  You control the game; the game doesn't control you!  Otherwise the game consists of saving the same characters OVER AND OVER AGAIN to accumulate replays to move on.  FRUSTRATING IN THE EXTREME.  If your ego or pride won't let you play on EASY, even tho it makes no difference any other way, then you get exactly what you deserve."
