76561197972118795,Not Recommended,214250,13801415,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,All American,"Frustrated beyond reason.The Good:- Ambiance: The world is in gritty ruin. It has a nice post-apocalyptic feel, and the grainy ""cam"" effect is a nice touch.- Sound: Not a big sound guy, but nothing to complain about here. The sound feels right for this type of game.- Music: Again, not a big game music guy, but the music works.- Controls: The controls feel solid and responsive, for the little bit I've been able to play/tolerate the game. Which leads me to...The Bad:- GRAPHICS!!!!!!!: Honestly, the game doesn't look bad. That's not the problem here. The problem is the graphics are so #$%^ing glitchy, fractured, and spotty that the game is almost entirely unplayable. Certainly a great many people haven't had problems, but I've found a great many people who have! Walls, floors, objects, textures, lighting... you name it, all these things randomly seem to disappear and reappear on my system. I have gone over multiple suggested methods on how to fix the graphics in ""I Am Alive"", and none of them have worked. The only one I haven't tried is going back to an older version of my NVidia drivers. If you have to install old drivers for this game to work, the developers (UBISOFT) didn't make a very solid title, nor do they give two squirts of♥♥♥♥♥♥about fixing this broken game.If the graphics actually WORKED for me, I would probably be recommending this title. Unfortunately, they do not. They make me want to slap the developers in the face with a crowbar until they are unrecognizeable as human.You may have better luck than I. Purchase at your own risk. If you suspect, even for a moment, that you may find yourself pulling your hair out trying to fix the graphics on this game, I recommend you don't pay more than $5 for this title.THE INFORMATION HEREAFTER HAS BEEN ADDED, AFTER THE GAME BECAME PLAYABLEI recently upgraded my graphics card from an older GTX 275 to a shiny new GTX 970. Please note, I did not change my view of this game from negative to positive. It makes me a little sad. So, here goes:The Good:- Nothing to add to my previous review information. Sadly, the game did not get better once I was able to play it. Instead, I was able to play it and see more bad.The Bad:- THE GRAPHICS!!!! Yes, I know I posted that complaint before, but now it's for an entirely different reason. It could be that my new video card is just TOO GOOD for this game, but now that I can actually see and play the game, it looks like garbage! What I thought was cool, atmospheric effects before has since been revealed to be an attempt at distracting you from lazy, sloppy game design. The models are clunky. The environments are bland. The actual object textures are not good in the least.- Pathing: I get not wanting the player to explore certain areas, but they should block those areas off better. I find myself constantly scratching my head as to why some of the minor obstacles in this game are insurmountable for the protagonist. This guy does plenty of acrobatic stunts when the game wants him to, but none of that pertains to those times when he's on flat ground with no risk of death looming over his head (or below his feet).- Stamina: I get that this is supposed to be a tough, survival type game, but our protagonist has no stamina whatsoever. It's quite annoying.- Combat: This has got to be the most counter-intuitive version of combat the studio could have possibly concocted. Some of it is fun, like being able to bluff enemies with an empty gun, but some of it makes no sense, like how you can't pull out your machete unless you're about to engage in combat, and it's basically worthless in a real fight.- Ammuntion: I get that it's scarce. That makes sense. But I hate when a game makes ammo extremely scarce and rare, but enemies have an endless supply (or at least, in theory). And if they do have a seemingly endless supply, when you finally kill them, they must have just shot their last bullet! They never drop but maybe one or two bullets. What the heck!?Overall, I feel this game had lots of potential, but just fell short in too many areas. It may be a fun game for some, and to those who enjoy it, more power to you. For me, however, I believe I've played all I'm ever going to of this game. I will not finish it."
