,Recommended,214250,3344974,"Posted: 31 January, 2013",all,Massacyre,"This game. It's...well it's different. If you like survival games then you should enjoy the bleak atmosphere and setting, but as the levels aren't massively open world, looking for supplies only requires you to take the less obvious route to your goal.Gunplay (and later on, arrow play) requires thinking and timing, as you only have 1 bullet vs 4 enemies at many points in the game. Again this adds a survival aspect to the game. If you are a fan of bleak miserable stories, then also conisder buying this game. It is one of the few arcade games that actually has a decent story.The thing this game is probably most well known for, and hated for, is the retry system. You pick up ""retries"" through the game by helping people, (by giving them your supplies) or just finding them lying about. Retries basically let you start from last saved checkpoint. Out of retries? Then you will have to start that level that you have been playing for an hour all over again. It's quite similar to Dead Space 2's Hardcore mode, where you only get a few saves (albeit not as harsh).The last gameplay element I will look over is the most important, and may influence you buying it. The stamina bar. The stamina bar is used up for almost anything except walking. It regenerates very quickly but only when walking. If you are halfway up a building, you can't just stop and rest, you either use up precious supplies, or die. When your stamina bar is empty you enter a mode called ""extreme effort"" which lets you push on through whatever you are doing (climbing, walking through dust clouds etc.) but then actually drains the capacity of your bar, which means less stamina regenerates each time you rest. This therefore, means climing is more supply dependant, unless you refill your bar to full capacity. For people who tend to not think things through before doing something, this game will not be for you. Unless you don't mind starting a level over every time you die.I played the game on the hardest difficulty from the outset and have only died 5 times between level 1 and 11, so it is easily done.In conclusion, this game I recommend on sale, as it only lasts about 5 hours but the story and satisfaction of surviving will make sure you do not regret the price.Story: 8/10 Graphics: 6/10 Gameplay: 8/10I give it overall, a solid 8/10."
