,Recommended,214250,9185091,"Posted: 19 February, 2014",all,bryanhbell,"I played about half of this game before getting sidetracked by other games. I have not yet returned to the game, but plan to eventually.There are three difficulty levels: Easy, Normal, and Survivor. I started out playing on Easy, but it was an unsatisfying experience. Then I played on the Survivor level, which was quite challenging, but more interesting and fun since resources (bullets, food, medicine) were scarce and I had to think carefully about whether or not to use each and when. The two biggest challenges were conserving my stamina as I climbed around and battling other survivors when they appeared in groups.The game does have a few problems. Most significant is the checkpoint save system. You cannot save your progress in the game yourself. Instead, the game saves your progress once you pass certain predetermined points. It's difficult to tell when these points will occur (or even when they have occurred) and they don't always occur when you might expect. They're also too widely spaced. This has the effect of intensifying your desire to push forward, but it also means you'll spend a fair amount of time retracing your recent progress.The control of your character, particularly when climbing, is sometimes glitchy and too unforgiving. There were many instances when I attempted to change direction during a climb and failed to do so because the character doesn't react quickly enough to the controls. The stamina mechanic, which limits the time you can spend climbing, can make this problem frustrating.You do not have complete freedom to take actions like jumping, climbing, or crouching. You'll be able to climb a fence or jump up on a crate in one area but you won't be able to do so in other identical areas. This intensifies the feeling that your progress through the game is predetermined and ""on rails"".Despite these problems, the game is engrossing. The visuals, voice acting, and atmosphere do a good job of drawing you into the game's post-apocalyptic world. Overall, I'd say the game serves up adequate, but not stellar, entertainment value. I bought the game during Steam's winter sale for $5 and so far feel like I'm getting my money's worth, but I don't think the game is worth more than $10.tl;dr Play the game on hardest difficulty for the best experience. The game's advantages (engrossing atmosphere and novel gameplay mechanics) are held back by some faults (a checkpoint save system, control issues, and lack of freedom) that result in the game being a fair, but not fantastic, value. Worth it for $5 but not at more than $10."
