76561198037377133,Not Recommended,214250,33500050,Posted: 13 July,all,Georgek117,"A pretty niche game that feels undeveloped, lacks much depth, and is pretty linear. At first I wasn't sure about it; the story wasn't exactly imaginative, it borrowed elements from lots of other games (Splinter Cell, Assassins Creed and Silent Hill I believe!), and had a pretty forgettable plot. At first the game seems challenging but once you've stockpiled a ton of consumables and learned the basic strategy that'll get you through every single fight, you've essentially beaten the game and it isn't very challenging anymore.That saying, the further I played the more I started to enjoy it, even though it is very short (5-6 hours). It's very atmospheric and creepy, and the map has a kind of large central area which you can explore and climb various buildings in, between mission waypoints. There are various nps you can collect resources to help out. But it's not a groundbreaking game by any means, and mine frequently crashed - forcing me to replay entire chapters. Unfortunately I think this game is destined to be forgotten and will undoubtedly be left unplayed in the majority of most players' libraries (I had my copy for 4 years before I played it), if even bought/downloaded at all.It might appeal to a bunch of people, just be prepared to have some patience with the crappy Steam port."
