,Not Recommended,214250,24822782,"Posted: 11 August, 2016",all,"God, owner of the Universe","THIS GAME SCORES [0 *1* | 2 3] = ~38% (25%-50%)(Might even only be 1of4, but I haven't seen enough of the game to judge.)""I Am Alive"" could have been good, but my experiences suggest that its game design in general is just bad.I get the ammo shortage idea, but the result the first time I came across it was this: 1) I had one bullet. Encountered a situation where I couldn't figure out a solution other than firing that one bullet. 2) Ten minutes later, I was at a fence or something, and crawling through the hole started a cutscene that I had no way of knowing would happen (So, my survival that supposedly depends on my decisions and how I balance stuff suddenly was very obviously tied to arbitrary game designer choices.), and when the cutscene was over, I wasinsidethe fenced area and had only seconds to save my life. That's really bad game design by itself (just sucking me in there without a warning, when the rest of the game screams ""This is a simulation!Youact and decide!""), but on top of that:The situation that unfoldedseemeddynamic, but no matter how hard I tried to avoid it: I got shot dead. Running/hiding was no option. So, since I had used my one bullet already in a situation that called for it, I was now stuck in a ""5 attempts left ... no, 4 ... 3"" loop that was just pure frustration, and it was at that time that a suspicion grew to certainty: This game is actually bad.When I tried again, I respawned a lot earlier in the game, so in combination with the accumulated frustration and the reasonable estimate that the rest of the game would have more such crappy game design decisions, I abandoned it entirely. Would have been a refund, but back then we didn't have that luxury yet.Btw., the very gimmicky and tediously slow climbing-on-rails situations didn't help, either."
