,Recommended,214250,2011769,"Posted: 4 January, 2013",all,Captain Quattro,"Overall, the game was good.I Am Alive features unique survival gameplay that is able to stand alone among similar games in the genre. Resources are scarce, combat is challenging, and the world seems to have a heavy, oppressive feel to it.The game features a clever climbing system where the player must utilize stamina effectively, and a unique combat system that attepts to humanize the enemies.Although the gameplay is fantastic it's storyline is not. It is short, only four or five hours long, and left me dissatisfied and empty (this meaning that there was no clear resolution to the story). But, despite that fact, I would still give the game a  7/10 or 8/10.It is worth a playthrough. But wait to get it while its on sale."
,Recommended,214250,4191823,"Posted: 29 December, 2012",all,Valassi,"An excellent, relatively short game (5-9 hours) characterized by realistic-looking post-apocalyptic settings that are quite stunning to behold. The level of attention to detail is downright impressive and really helps to immerse you within its story that is rather simple at its core but is enhanced by endearing moments & characters that feel and act like living, breathing human beings. I found that I cared about the main character's plight and mission and was invested in trying to make this hellish future into a better place by saving an adorable little girl, helping to reunite her with her absent mother, encountering other survivors and aiding them when I could and murdering opportunistic SOBs that preyed on the weak and innocent, JUSTICE IS SERVED beeyatches! xDThe gameplay itself is well-balanced with platforming elements that emphasize managing your limited stamina during its many awe-inspiring climbing portions that have you scaling the side of unmaintained skycrappers, clambering across elevated scaffolding and more while using pistons to pause and recuperate at opportune moments. It made these sections feel tense, as close to reality that a game can get and a lot of fun.Finally, the combat is also quite well-done as you can make charging gang members halt in their tracks by whipping out a gun, frightening them into holding their hands up as you either use this opportunity to back them into hazardous elements of the environments which is always a riot to watch unfold or blast them apart with well-placed shots. This is especially fun as you can do this while out of ammo but take too long and your opponents will wise up and charge you.9/10"
