,Recommended,214250,14759910,"Posted: 6 March, 2015",all,Jakob Kierkegaard,"This is one of those games I enjoyed playing but I equally enjoy having completed it.The post-apocalyptic environment is well built and you really get into the mood of the game. It's a depressing and gritty game and the designers have been spot on with creating the setting.You spend a lot of time running around and climbing. The climbing mechanics works quite well; you climb in a manner similar to that of AC, but with the added feature that you have limited stamina that decreases while climbing. This means that you only have a limited time climbing before you have to find a secure spot to recover stamina if you don't want to risk dying mid-climb. It's a feature that I actually ended up loving as it added a (slightly) realistic pressure on an otherwise very generic climbing functionality.The game is probably the closest you'll get to Last of Us on PC.The graphics on the technical side is mediocre at best. It's clearly a console port and had a bit of extra work been put into the title the graphics could have been so much better.The camera angles - my god. You are not able to zoom out when moving around and you're stuck to the neck all the time and I didn't feel any potential overview being lost. With that said; when climbing large buildings the camera zooms out (some times) to give you a better over of the surrounding routes.The mouse controls are... wonky. Weird sensitivity and it feels sluggish.The groups of enemies you meet are often same combinations as previous encounters, meaning that encounters, though challenging due to very limited resources, become routine.Very linear.Despite the concept of the game was/is great and I loved it, the technical issues and repetitions made it at the same time feel a bit... off. Had you asked me during a gaming session whether I would recommend it or not I'd probably say no. Looking back at it now I'd say yes. In the end it all depends on how accepting you are of the technical limitations of the game."
