76561198000147308,Recommended,214250,20864769,"Posted: 30 January, 2016",all,Raashk,"So I recommend this game with extreme caveats. If you want to see a really good IDEA for a game, this is a decent pick-up. I think this is a good look for game developers looking to see how scavenging mechanics can be implemented fairly well. Ammo is scarce, climbing is dangerous and your supply of safety equipment is extremely limited, and still this game gives you a way to complete challenges. The atmosphere is very well done and the world is quite immersive (if you can excuse some of the control issues).THAT BEING SAID:  (SPOILERS)This game is unfinished and will never be finished. There is no real story arc other than some amorphous bull about finding someone missing that will never come to fruition for the player.  Controls, as mentioned are frustrating to learn, and even once mastered, can easily be screwed up by happenstance (like, trying to jump somewhere but instead leaping to your death).If you don't go into this game expecting a full, round, complete experience, you'll be better off for it, BUT this game will give you an interesting experience that I haven't really gotten from many other games."
